    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-09-17T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-09-17T03:00:00-05:00" n="568"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d568">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">357.AD/9–1751: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Korea</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Muccio</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Pusan</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-09-17T17:00:00+09:00"
                            >September 17, 1951—5 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>256. Ref <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 208, Sept 12. Concur Dept’s
                    view that under present circumstances with <gloss target="#t_UNC1">UNC</gloss>
                    operating agency of UN for indefinite period it desirable to proceed with
                    negotiation <gloss target="#t_CINCUNC1">CINCUNC</gloss>–<gloss target="#t_ROK1"
                        >ROK</gloss> agreement, including control by <gloss target="#t_CINCUNC1"
                        >CINCUNC</gloss> over <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> foreign exchange,
                    with editorial changes suggested your msg. Further recommend that when
                    legislation now before Congress is passed relieving <gloss target="#t_ECA1"
                        >ECA</gloss> responsibility for counterpart funds and other residual
                    functions under agreement on aid that responsibility these functions be
                    transferred from Embassy to <gloss target="#t_CINCUNC1">CINCUNC</gloss>.</p>
                <p>Successful conclusion of negotiations for payment of <gloss target="#t_ROK1"
                        >ROK</gloss> of dollars reed from <hi rend="italic">won</hi> sales to UN
                    personnel prior opening discuscussions on <gloss target="#t_CINCUNC1"
                        >CINCUNC</gloss>–<gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> agreement might create
                    more favorable atmosphere for these discussions. If negotiators authorized to
                    agree to wipe out <gloss target="#t_ECA1">ECA</gloss> counterpart fund by
                    application on <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> overdraft, as previously
                    proposed by Embassy, believe this too might assist in expediting conclusion
                    satisfactory <gloss target="#t_CINCUNC1">CINCUNC</gloss>–<gloss target="#t_ROK1"
                        >ROK</gloss> agreement. Negotiators shld be prepared demonstrate that all
                    possible steps being taken to increase flow of supplies for sale on Korean
                    market since danger of runaway inflation now matter of utmost concern to
                    responsible <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> officials.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Muccio</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
